About Us






















Since 2001, Brookside Mezzanine Partners has maintained a successful track record of identifying attractive investment opportunities across the lower-middle U.S. market.  





Investment Criteria




Brookside Mezzanine Partners specializes in subordinated debt and minority equity investments in leading, small to mid-sized companies based in the United States. While the Firm does not have a specific industry or geographic focus, we generally invest in manufacturing, business services, distribution, restaurant/retail and healthcare companies.
 
The companies in which we invest typically exhibit the following attributes:
 

EBITDA of at least $3 million
Revenue of at least $15 million
EBITDA margins in excess of 10%
Stable historical performance and predictable cash flows
Strong management
Defensible market positions
Industry leaders


We invest in both sponsored and non-sponsored transactions and provide junior capital to finance the following needs:
 

Strategic acquisitions
Buyouts
Leveraged recapitalizations
Dividend payments
Growth capital


We look forward to discussing new transactions with you and promise a prompt and confidential reply.








 




















 




















